      "id": "oasis",
      "icon": "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
      "name": "OASIS Signup",
      "description": "Creates oasis.os.fan (Oasis fan) accounts end to end: enters the email, ticks the required marketing consent, fills whichever sign-up details the site asks for, and saves the account on success. Fully proxy-geo aware - the city/town, phone number, and dialing country all follow wherever the run's proxy exits, and the page's own language is handled automatically (locale-independent, so it works on any-country proxies). Date of birth is random but always 18+. Name and email come from the run profile's identity. The form varies between runs, so only the fields actually shown get filled - it handles a location on its own, names without a location, or the full form. If the email has already joined, the site jumps past the form and the module clicks through and still records the account, without adding a duplicate row for an email already saved. Fails fast with a clear message if the email is already registered or the proxy geo can't be resolved.",
      "version": "1.3.2",
